C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\codex_final_audit.session.log:504:[codex] 108:Internal motivation to respond without prejudice. To assess internal motives (e.g., image concerns) in the final author selection, we adapted four items from Plant and DevineΓÇÖs (1998) internal motivation to respond without prejudice scale (e.g., ΓÇ£Given my personal values and beliefs, an important factor in my selection of the seventh author to add to my list was my desire to promote the success of racial minorities.ΓÇ¥; CronbachΓÇÖs ╬▒ = 0.93). Items used a  1 (Strongly disagree) to 7 (Strongly agree) scale and, as pre-registered, were separately z-scored and then averaged.
C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\codex_final_audit.session.log:505:[codex] 109:External motivation to respond without prejudice. To assess external motives (e.g., reputational concerns) in the final author selection,  we adapted three items from Plant and DevineΓÇÖs external motivation to respond without prejudice scale (e.g., ΓÇ£When making my decision about who to select as my seventh author, I considered the social pressures I face to appear to promote racial minorities where they are typically underrepresented.ΓÇ¥; CronbachΓÇÖs ╬▒ = 0.90). Items used a 1 (Strongly disagree) to 7 (Strongly agree) scale, and as pre-registered, were separately z-scored and then averaged. 
C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\codex_final_audit.session.log:509:[codex] 113:We next tested for both mediators in a multiple mediation model (as preregistered), which addressed address potential multicollinearity between these correlated measures (rΓÇë=ΓÇë0.72, p < 0.001). Once accounting for the correlation between constructs, internal motivation to respond without prejudice (indirect effect = 0.08, 95% CI = [0.042, 0.11]), significantly mediated the effect  whereas external motivation to respond without prejudice (indirect effect = -0.014, 95% CI = [-0.03, 0.00]) did not.  
