C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\codex_session.log:402:[codex] We next tested for both mediators in a multiple mediation model (as preregistered), which addressed address potential multicollinearity between these correlated measures (rΓÇë=ΓÇë0.72, p < 0.001). Once accounting for the correlation between constructs, internal motivation to respond without prejudice (indirect effect = 0.08, 95% CI = [0.042, 0.11]), significantly mediated the effect  whereas external motivation to respond without prejudice (indirect effect = -0.014, 95% CI = [-0.03, 0.00]) did not.  
