C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\codex_zero_baseline_round3.md:37:We further considered the possibility that participants may have already used the comparison attributes appropriately in their initial selections, leaving less room for descriptive feedback about those attributes to change subsequent choices. We report a pooled zero-baseline analysis in Appendix Section S[X] that restricts attention to cases in which participants initially selected zero options with a given attribute. This provides a conservative test of whether feedback about an attribute’s complete absence produces the same pattern for race and gender as for the other attributes summarized in our studies.
