C:\Users\jcerv\Jose\diversity_feedback\revision-analysis\_r2_review\r2_gdoc_text.txt:45:Notes. This table reports the OLS treatment effect of receiving feedback about the focal attribute on the rate of selecting a candidate with that attribute on the participant’s final selection, restricted to participants whose initial selection contained zero of the focal attribute. Per-cell estimates use HC3 robust standard errors. The pooled rows come from a single OLS model with study fixed effects and standard errors clustered by participant; the final row is a Wald test of the difference between the pooled race and gender and pooled comparison coefficients in that model. Confidence intervals are 95%. +p < .10; *p < .05; **p < .01; ***p < .001.
